    "pokemonName": {
      "en": "Corphish",
      "cn": "龙虾小兵"
    },
    "setName": "[XY] Dragon Dance",
    "description": "Moves\nDragon Dance boosts Corphish's Attack and Speed, allowing it to sweep quite easily late-game. Crabhammer is its primary STAB move, doing tons of damage when backed by Adaptability and a possible Dragon Dance boost. Knock Off provides solid neutral coverage alongside Crabhammer and can be used to cripple switch-ins early-game. Aqua Jet gives Corphish more utility before it sets up and allows it to pick off weakened Choice Scarf or priority users after setting up. Aerial Ace is a less useful option in the last slot, but it will ensure that Corphish is not completely walled by Croagunk (although Corphish will have to be healthy, and Croagunk without its Eviolite, for Corphish to actually beat it); it also deals a decent amount of damage to Eviolite-less Foongus and Cottonee. Superpower can deal with weakened Ferroseed and Lileep, but the given moves are generally more useful.\nSet Details\nThe given EVs best bring out Corphish's sweeping potential by maximizing its Attack and Speed, with the remaining EVs in Defense to hit an Eviolite number. A Jolly nature is used to hit 14 Speed so that Corphish can outspeed 19 and 20 Speed Pokemon such as Abra, Taillow, Elekid, and Diglett after a boost; however, if you are confident in removing Staryu and in getting Stealth Rock up to ensure that Aqua Jet OHKOes Elekid and Taillow, an Adamant nature noticeably benefits Corphish's damage rolls; most other 19 and 20 Speed Pokemon fear Aqua Jet regardless. Eviolite is the preferred item, as it gives Corphish the bulk to survive a number of would-be OHKOs and set up. Life Orb is a viable alternative, as it grants Corphish an enormous amount of power after a Dragon Dance, cleanly OHKOing defensive Porygon after Stealth Rock provided Corphish has an Adamant nature and OHKOing Fletchling with a +1 Aqua Jet. However, the loss of bulk makes it much more difficult to actually get the boosts; additionally, if Life Orb is used, Corphish's HP IV should be reduced to 13. Berry Juice is a decent choice if you want Corphish to try to set up more than one Dragon Dance, but the lack of immediate bulk can be troublesome.\nUsage Tips\nIt is usually best to have Corphish set up late in the match, after its checks, which include Foongus, Croagunk, Chinchou, Magnemite, and Cottonee, have been heavily weakened or removed. Despite this, Corphish possesses a great deal of utility with Knock Off and strong priority, which can be useful throughout the match. Corphish can support its own sweep by removing its checks' items with Knock Off earlier on in the match.\nTeam Options\nUnlike other variants of Corphish, Dragon Dance Corphish is usually used as the dedicated sweeper in Water-type spam cores, although it is still effective as a wallbreaker thanks to Knock Off and its overall enormous damage output. Good choices for Water-type spam partners include Carvanha, Tirtouga, and Omanyte. Gothita and Diglett are able to trap and weaken or KO many of Corphish's checks, such as Croagunk and Chinchou. As with all offensive Pokemon, entry hazard support helps Corphish obtain notable KOs and wear down the opposition; Ferroseed in particular handles many of Corphish's checks, but it may forfeit momentum on offensive teams.",
