    "pokemonName": {
      "en": "Corphish",
      "cn": "龙虾小兵"
    },
    "setName": "[SM] Wallbreaker",
    "description": "Moves\nCrabhammer is an extremely powerful STAB attack which, thanks to Adaptability, hits insanely hard, dealing a lot of damage to even Pokemon that resist it. Aqua Jet is a powerful priority move that allows Corphish to pick off weakened threats and can allow it to sweep with a Swords Dance boost. Knock Off allows Corphish to remove items such as Eviolite and Choice Scarf and weaken its checks such as Foongus and Chinchou. Swords Dance boosts Corphish's Attack, making it into a massive threat that can at worst 2HKO most of the LC metagame.\nSet Details\nAdaptability is used to boost Corphish's STAB attacks, making it into a fearsome wallbreaker. The EV spread maximizes Attack and Speed, reaching 18 Attack and 13 Speed, which allows Corphish to attack as hard as possible while still being able to outspeed walls such as defensive Mudbray and Spritzee. Eviolite is used to increase Corphish's bulk, giving it more opportunities to set up. Adamant is used to maximize Attack, allowing Corphish to hit as hard as possible.\nUsage Tips\nRemoving enemy items such as Berry Juice and Eviolite can be very helpful for Corphish and its teammates, so try to hit opposing switch-ins with Knock Off. Try to keep Corphish alive against bulkier teams, as it can deal with those types of teams well thanks to its ability to wallbreak. Use Swords Dance to clean up when the enemy team is at low health near the end of a game, or use it near the beginning to put large holes in the enemy team to allow the rest of your team to clean up. Corphish can take advantage of the switches that it forces to set up Swords Dance.\nTeam Options\nCorphish can help wallbreak for other Water-type sweepers such as Tirtouga, Omanyte, and Carvanha, which all appreciate the Knock Off support that Corphish gives. Corphish has no way to recover health, and as such cannot recover from entry hazard damage, so a way to get rid of hazards is wanted. Staryu is a very reliable spinner that can get rid of entry hazards for Corphish. Diglett can trap and KO Chinchou and can also KO Cottonee with Sludge Bomb, two Pokemon that are able to check Corphish. Corphish appreciates Sticky Web support, as it slows down the enemy team, allowing it to outspeed a number of Pokemon, such as Mienfoo and Elekid, and deal tons of damage. Grass-type checks are helpful, as many Grass-types are able to threaten Corphish. Ponyta, Vullaby, and Rufflet are all able to check Grass-types. Hazard setters such as Ferroseed and Dwebble deal residual damage to enemy Pokemon, allowing Corphish to pick up more KOs.",
