    "setName": "[SM] Dragon Dance",
    "description": "Moves\nCrabhammer is Corphish's most powerful STAB move. Aqua Jet picks off weakened Pokemon before Corphish obtains a Dragon Dance boost. Knock Off allows Corphish to remove items such as Eviolite and Choice Scarf and weaken its checks, such as Foongus and Chinchou. Aerial Ace can be used to hit Grass-types such as Foongus, and Cottonee, and Croagunk, which are otherwise immune to or resist all of Corphish's attacks. However, Corphish will have to give up Aqua Jet, which means that it cannot hit Choice Scarf users that outspeed it after a Dragon Dance boost. Dragon Dance boosts both Attack and Speed, making Corphish into a scary sweeper that can clean up late-game.\nSet Details\nAdaptability is used to boost Corphish's STAB attacks, making it into a fearsome wallbreaker. The EVs maximize Attack and Speed while allowing Corphish's Defense to hit an Eviolite number. A Jolly nature is used to reach 14 Speed, which after a Dragon Dance, lets Corphish reach 21 Speed, which outspeeds the entire unboosted LC metagame. An Adamant nature leaves Corphish to tie with 19 Speed Pokemon such as Staryu and outsped by Elekid and Diglett after a boost, but noticeably increases its damage. Eviolite is used to give Corphish more bulk, giving it a better chance of setting up, and allowing Corphish to take priority attacks better as well.\nUsage Tips\nBe careful when using Corphish early-game, as it can be easily worn down, making it harder to set up later in the game. Use Corphish late-game to sweep after checks such as Foongus, Cottonee, and Croagunk are weakened. Corphish can be used to weaken its own checks with Knock Off early in the game. Use Aqua Jet to pick off weakened or frail opposing Pokemon.\nTeam Options\nOther Water-type sweepers such as Tirtouga, Omanyte, and Carvanha can help weaken mutual checks so that Corphish can sweep. Diglett can trap and KO most of Corphish's checks such as Croagunk, Chinchou, and Cottonee with Sludge Bomb. Entry hazards help weaken the enemy team to give Corphish a better chance of sweeping; Ferroseed and Dwebble are two good options for this. Wallbreakers can help Corphish break through walls a lot better, such as Ice Punch Timburr, which can lure in and defeat Grass-types such as Cottonee and Foongus.",
