    "pokemonName": {
      "en": "Frillish",
      "cn": "轻飘飘"
    },
    "setName": "[SM] Choice Scarf + Water Spout",
    "description": "Moves\nWater Spout is insanely strong, and with Choice Scarf Frillish can outspeed the entire unboosted metagame and deal tons of damage. Shadow Ball allows Frillish to deal neutral damage to most Pokemon, giving it a safe option. It also allows Frillish to hit Ghost- and Psychic-types that can threaten it, such as Honedge, Gastly, and Abra. Hydro Pump is another safe option when Frillish is at low health, and Frillish does not mind losing Shadow Ball because it does not hit many Pokemon super effectively. Ice Beam is able to hit Grass-types that resist Water Spout, such as Pumpkaboo-XL, Snivy, and Foongus. Energy Ball is able to hit Water-types that resist Water Spout such as Chinchou and Staryu. Trick lets Frillish cripple walls that enjoy switching into it, such as Munchlax, Foongus, and Spritzee.\nSet Details\nRunning 196 Speed EVs allows Frillish to reach 14 Speed and outspeed the entire unboosted metagame with a Choice Scarf equipped. 236 Special Attack EVs maximize Frillish's damage, and the rest of the EVs are put into HP to increase longevity. Water Absorb allows Frillish to switch into Water-type attacks for free and can also help Water Spout do more damage by restoring HP.\nUsage Tips\nFrillish can help break holes into the opposing team to allow for its teammates to clean up. Frillish can also clean up opposing teams once its checks and counters have been weakened a bit thanks to its Choice Scarf. Make sure to play around the opponent's hazard setter if they have one because hazards make Water Spout weaker. Frillish can spinblock, but it can lose a good amount of HP if it switches into an attack, which will make Water Spout weaker. Try to not directly switch into any attacks, as that will weaken Water Spout's damage.\nTeam Options\nDefog and Rapid Spin are necessary, as Water Spout is weakened by hazard damage. Vullaby and Staryu are both good options. Chinchou is a major problem for Frillish, so Diglett is a good partner, as it is able to trap and KO Chinchou. Grass-types such as Cottonee and Foongus are also able to deal with Chinchou. Frillish does not appreciate taking Knock Off, so teammates that can take Knock Off well, such as Mienfoo and Trubbish, are good. Dark-types threaten Frillish, so Fighting-types such as Mienfoo and Timburr are good partners. Entry hazard setters such as Dwebble, Omanyte, Ferroseed, and Onix all appreciate Frillish, as it is able to spinblock, which prevents the foe from spinning away hazards. Slow pivots such as Mienfoo and Chinchou can bring Frillish in without taking any damage, which allows it to fire off powerful Water Spouts.",
