    "setName": "[BW] Lead",
    "description": "Kabuto is a good lead because it has access to both Stealth Rock and\npriority in Aqua Jet, which helps Kabuto get rid of Focus Sash on\nopposing leads, as well as stopping the effect of Sturdy. STAB Rock\nSlide hits hard and has good coverage with Aqua Jet. Rapid Spin allows\nKabuto to support its team by getting rid of troublesome entry hazards\nthat might cripple a teammate, and can also finish off badly weakened\nPokemon. Protect is useful for scouting and blocking Fake Out.\nFocus Sash allows Kabuto to survive strong attacks which might OHKO\nKabuto otherwise. Eviolite can also be used, as leading is harder with\nTeam Preview. Waterfall is a viable option over Rock Slide as it hits\nFighting- and Ground-type Pokemon harder, such as Hippopotas, Timburr,\nand Drilbur. It can also be used as a replacement for Rapid Spin as it\ngives Kabuto more coverage. Pokemon that can set up Rain Dance, such as\nBronzor and Frillish, are good partners for Kabuto. Fast Pokemon such as\nAipom or Voltorb can also set up Rain Dance.",
