    "setName": "[SM] Life Orb",
    "description": "Moves\nTail Slap is a powerful STAB move that does significant damage to anything that does not resist it due to LC damage mechanics. For example, it 2HKOes Spritzee, Foongus, and Vullaby. Knock Off allows Minccino to hit Ghost-types and remove the foe's item to help itself or a teammate. Seed Bomb can be run to hit Rock-types such as Onix and Tirtouga. U-turn can give Minccino a way out of unfavorable matchups or as a way of gaining offensive momentum. Wake-Up Slap gives Minccino a way to hit Steel-types, such as Pawniard and Ferroseed, super effectively.\nSet Details\nMinccino's Speed is maximized to allow it to outspeed Mienfoo and Onix while Speed tying with Gastly and Doduo. Life Orb is used as its item to massively increase the damage output of Tail Slap. The remaining EVs are invested in Defense and Special Defense to boost both its defenses by as much as possible, which slightly increases its longevity. Skill Link is used to force Tail Slap to always hit five times, giving it more consistent damage output than Technician would.\nUsage Tips\nMinccino generally works best as an early-game breaker, dealing heavy damage to defensive foes to allow a partner to clean. Due to its poor defensive stats, Minccino should not be switched directly into an attack; instead, use a pivoting move such as Mienfoo's U-turn or Magnemite's Volt Switch to bring it in. Minccino can also be used to force out Weak Armor Vullaby, Eviolite Snivy, and Onix with any chip damage.\nTeam Options\nEntry hazard setters such as Ferroseed work very well with Minccino, since a layer of Spikes and Stealth Rock can provide enough chip damage on defensive foes for Minccino to OHKO them. Mienfoo, Vullaby, and Magnemite all work well with Minccino by using Volt Switch and U-turn to get it in without taking damage. Diglett and Magnemite can help Minccino to clean by trapping common Steel-types such as Pawniard, Ferroseed, and Magnemite, while Minccino can weaken defensive Pokemon down to a point where they can be trapped. Fighting-type checks such as Spritzee and Foongus give Minccino a way out of a Fighting-type matchup. Switch-ins to Steel- and Rock-types such as Mienfoo are helpful, since Minccino struggles to OHKO most of them and many of them will KO in return. Minccino pairs well with Fighting-types such as Mienfoo and Timburr, since it can do heavy damage to their checks such as Spritzee and Foongus, allowing them to clean.",
