    "description": "This set aims to set up Hone Claws on Pokemon unable to really hurt Nidoran-M, such as defensive Spritzee and non-Spore Foongus, and break through the opposing team while using Sucker Punch to nab faster threats. However, finding this type of setup opportunity is difficult, and Nidoran-M can still be easily stopped by defensive Ground-types and faster threats that can deal with Sucker Punch. Pokemon such as Croagunk, Rufflet, and Pawniard are much more useful, as they each individually have a much easier time setting up and breaking through opposing teams.",
