    "setName": "[BW] Wallbreaker",
    "description": "When equipped with Swords Dance, Pawniard can leverage its solid STAB attacks, good coverage, and extremely powerful priority in Sucker Punch to cleave through defense and offense alike. Although Pawniard is still frail even when outfitted with Eviolite, its Dark / Steel typing has plenty of resistances, giving Pawniard setup opportunities against passive walls like Wormadam-S, Vullaby, and Clefairy lacking Thunder Wave. Pawniard can also set up on weaker physical attackers like Persian and Emolga and Choice-locked Pokemon like Mr. Mime, Grumpig, and Gastly. Pawniard's STAB Sucker Punch is a strong priority move that staves off frail would-be revenge killers like Simisear and Raichu, outright OHKOing them after a Swords Dance even though they are not weak to it. STAB Iron Head complements Sucker Punch, breaking physically defensive Pokemon like Solrock and Graveler, circumventing the chance to fail Sucker Punch has, and potentially flinching down walls like Clefairy, Hippopotas, and Vibrava. Pursuit provides Pawniard offensive utility, picking off weakened Dark-weak Pokemon, like Choice-locked Mr. Mime, Grumpig, and Gastly. Offensive pivots like Persian and Emolga often lack the coverage to significantly damage Pawniard and thus are also vulnerable to Pursuit. Night Slash is a strong, reliable Dark-type STAB move to beat Steel-resistant walls like Frillish, which resists Iron Head and can deny Sucker Punch by using Will-O-Wisp. Low Kick lets Pawniard break Lairon, which otherwise tanks Pawniard's STAB moves.\nPawniard fits on offensive teams, as they appreciate Pawniard's wallbreaking, potential to sweep, and decent defensive profile for a wallbreaker. Fast cleaners like Simisear, Raichu, and Mr. Mime greatly appreciate Pawniard breaking down defensive cores for them. Offensive pivots like Persian and Emolga help bring Pawniard in safely while luring in physical walls like Wormdam-S and Solrock for Pawniard to break. Mienfoo is a significant problem for Pawniard, so Muk and Arbok make helpful partners, while Pawniard can protect them from offensive Psychic-types like Grumpig and Mr. Mime. Setup sweepers like Shelgon and Leafeon benefit from Pawniard softening up physical walls so that they can sweep.",
