    "setName": "[BW] Choice Scarf",
    "description": "Psyduck is a good Choice Scarf user, reaching 22 Speed while negating\nweather when on the field by using its ability. Hydro Pump is the\npreferred STAB move due to its power, but Surf is viable for its\naccuracy. Ice Beam hits Dragon- and Grass-types. In the third slot,\nHidden Power Fire is preferred, as it deals with the important Ferroseed\nand Snover. Hidden Power Grass is an option, however, if the team has\nproblems with Water-types. In the last slot, Signal Beam is used for\nextra coverage, hitting Slowpoke, which is useful if using Hidden Power\nFire, and also hitting Snover, which is important if using Hidden Power\nGrass.\nPsyduck could use a Timid nature for the extra Speed, but the power drop\nis unwelcome. Mud Bomb could be used if running Hidden Power Fire for\nhitting Chinchou, but Psyduck loses a bit of coverage by doing so. If\nnot using Mud Bomb or Hidden Power Grass, Chinchou can come in on any of\nPsyduck's moves and force it out. Ferroseed is a good teammate for\nPsyduck to beat Chinchou that lack Hidden Power Fire, while Dratini\nworks against versions lacking Ice Beam. Mantyke also easily takes\nanything that Psyduck dishes out, meaning that a Chinchou of your own\nworks well alongside Psyduck. Houndour and Ponyta are good options as\nwell, having excellent synergy with Psyduck, especially when used with a\nGrass-type such as Ferroseed or Lileep, forming a Fire / Water / Grass\ncore.",
